🧑‍💻💥[𝗫𝗦𝗦 𝗔𝘁𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗛𝗼𝗺𝗲-𝗟𝗮𝗯]💥👩‍💻
This lab is designed to test Cross-site Scripting attacks.
If you’re interested in becoming Security Tester, Pentester, Ethical Hacker, this lab will help you to detect and exploit reflected, stored and Dom-based XSS vulnerabilities.

🟢  𝐂𝐨𝐫𝐞 𝐈𝐧𝐠𝐫𝐞𝐝𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬
📌 Setup Virtual-box https://lnkd.in/d8Shs5VE
📌 Kali Linux https://lnkd.in/dH66DGFe
📌 Download WebGoat https://lnkd.in/dnUe9gMi

🟢  𝐃𝐞𝐭𝐞𝐜𝐭 𝐗𝐒𝐒 𝐕𝐮𝐥𝐧𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐛𝐢𝐥𝐢𝐭𝐢𝐞𝐬
In this section, we’ll detect XSS vulnerabilities using DalFox, XSStrike, XSS Scanner and Burp-Suite tools.
📌 Scanning for XSS using DalFox https://lnkd.in/dxAQsrnk
📌 Scanning with XSStrike Tool https://lnkd.in/d293QQjB
📌 Scanning with XSS Scanner https://lnkd.in/di4aQHxv


🟢 𝐄𝐱𝐚𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐞𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐗𝐒𝐒 𝐚𝐭𝐭𝐚𝐜𝐤𝐬
➡️ Reflected XSS into HTML context
➡️ Reflected XSS with event handlers
➡️ Reflected XSS with some SVG markup
➡️ Stored XSS
➡️ DOM-based XSS

🟢 𝐔𝐬𝐞 𝐂𝐚𝐬𝐞𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐗𝐒𝐒 𝐚𝐭𝐭𝐚𝐜𝐤𝐬
➡️ Exploiting cross-site scripting to steal cookies
➡️ Exploiting cross-site scripting to capture passwords
➡️ Exploiting cross-site scripting to perform CSRF
